title: Bug 49235: ServletContainerInitializer onStartup(Set<Class<? classSet is not expected class
description: Bug 49235: ServletContainerInitializer onStartup(Set<Class<? The output is "MySomeClass".
OB: When calling the onStartup() method of ServletContainerInitializer with a Set<Class<?>, the output is "MySomeClass".
SR:
To reproduce the issue:
1. Call the onStartup() method of ServletContainerInitializer.
2. Pass a Set<Class<?>> to the method.
3. Observe the output and verify that it is not "MySomeClass".
